# Semidefinite Programming Entanglement Detection (PPT Criterion)

## Overview
This project implements a semidefinite programming (SDP) formulation of entanglement detection in bipartite quantum systems using the Positive Partial Transpose (PPT) criterion.

## Theory
A quantum state ρ is valid if:
- ρ ⪰ 0 (positive semidefinite)
- Tr(ρ) = 1

For bipartite systems, separability implies:
- ρ^{T_B} ⪰ 0

Thus entanglement detection reduces to checking feasibility of an SDP with partial transpose constraints.

## Method
We formulate:
- density matrix constraints
- PPT positivity constraint
- numerical eigenvalue test

## Tools
- Python
- CVXPY
- NumPy

## Results
- Bell state detected as entangled (negative eigenvalue of partial transpose)
- Separable states satisfy PPT condition

